{"title": "penny magazine of the Society for the Diffusion of Useful Knowledge, issue 11", "description": "The Penny Magazine of the Society for the Diffusion of Useful Knowledge was published in competition to Chambers's Edinburgh Journal, which started two months earlier. Costing just one penny, it was aimed at the working class and needed broad circulation in order to survive. Initially successful, its content proved to miss the mark and be of more interest to the upper classes and folded after a couple of years. Its format was to offer short essays on a variety of topics the paternalistic publisher deemed important to its readership. - Summary by LynneT", "duration": 4230, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "3322", "name": "Charles Knight"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/usefulknowledge11_2602_librivox/PENNY_MAGAZINE11_2602.jpg", "copyright_year": "1832", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Lynne T"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Lynne T"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Lynne T"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Crocodile", "readers": [20394], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/usefulknowledge11_2602_librivox/usefulknowledge11_01_knight_64kb.mp3", "duration": 442}, {"section": 2, "title": "Statistical Notes -- England and Wales -- continued", "readers": [14624], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/usefulknowledge11_2602_librivox/usefulknowledge11_02_knight_64kb.mp3", "duration": 776}, {"section": 3, "title": "Singular Escape", "readers": [10244], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/usefulknowledge11_2602_librivox/usefulknowledge11_03_knight_64kb.mp3", "duration": 581}, {"section": 4, "title": "The British Museum No. 3", "readers": [20552], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/usefulknowledge11_2602_librivox/usefulknowledge11_04_knight_64kb.mp3", "duration": 582}, {"section": 5, "title": "Ca